<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;IMAGE_21_BIRD-0.JPG&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The category of this image feature block is 'organism'. The entity features are as follows:Organism Features:- **Species/Type:** The organism appears to be a large water bird, likely a cormorant or similar species, characterized by its dark plumage, long neck, and elongated body.- **Color:** The bird is predominantly dark-colored, appearing black or very dark blue/green, with a slight sheen or highlight on its feathers. There is a noticeable lighter, possibly yellowish or tan, patch on the underside of its beak and throat area.- **Shape:** It has a streamlined body, a long and slender neck, and a relatively small head with a distinct, pointed beak. Its legs are visible as two sturdy, dark vertical structures.- **Posture:** The bird is standing upright, with its long neck stretched almost vertically upwards. Its beak is open and pointed towards the sky, suggesting it might be calling, performing a display, or simply stretching. Its wings are folded against its body.- **Structural Characteristics:** The bird exhibits the typical features of a diving waterbird, with a strong, elongated neck and a robust body. The beak appears to be long and slightly hooked, though the detail is limited."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_21_BIRD-1.JPG&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The category of this image feature block is 'organism'. The entity features are as follows:Organism Features:- **Type:** Two birds, likely wading birds such as cranes or storks, characterized by their slender build.- **Color:** Their bodies appear very dark, almost black or deep grey/brown. Their beaks and possibly parts of their heads are a lighter, yellowish-brown or sandy color.- **Shape:** Both birds have long, elegant necks, elongated bodies, and long, thin legs.- **Posture:** They are standing upright, with their long necks extended upwards and their heads tilted slightly back, or their beaks pointing skyward. They are positioned very close to each other, almost mirroring each other's pose.- **Interaction:** The synchronized posture suggests they might be engaged in a courtship ritual, a display, or a synchronized movement.- **Number:** There are two distinct birds visible."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IMAGE_21&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image captures a serene and majestic natural scene, featuring four large birds, likely cranes or similar waterfowl, presented as dark silhouettes against a shimmering, golden body of water. The warm, radiant hues of the water suggest either sunrise or sunset, with colors ranging from bright golden yellow to soft orange, creating a tranquil and reflective surface. Three of the birds, positioned centrally and towards the right, stand tall with their long necks elegantly extended upwards, their beaks pointing towards the sky, conveying a sense of calling or observation. The fourth bird, located on the far left, has its head lowered, possibly engaging in preening or foraging in the shallow water. All four birds are standing in the water, which beautifully reflects their dark forms and the ambient golden light, with subtle ripples visible around their slender legs. The background is entirely composed of this luminous, reflective water, enhancing the dramatic silhouette effect of the birds. Across the very top of the image, a horizontal reddish-brown band contains the white, uppercase sans-serif text "ANNUAL PASS", suggesting the image might be part of a promotional material or a pass card."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANNUAL PASS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"White text displayed prominently on a dark red banner at the top of the image, indicating a type of entry or membership pass."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BANNER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A dark red rectangular banner positioned at the top of the image, serving as a header for the 'Annual Pass' text."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRANES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A group of four silhouetted cranes, dark in color, standing in shallow water. Three of the cranes have their heads raised, appearing to call, while one has its head lower. They are the central subject of the image."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WATER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A body of shallow water, appearing golden and shimmering, likely reflecting the light from the sky. The cranes are standing in this water."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REFLECTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dark, elongated mirror images of the cranes visible in the golden water beneath them."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_21.jpg</data>
</node>
